Class DefaultTypeCheckerProofNode

java.lang.Object
  de.unisiegen.tpml.core.AbstractProofNode
      de.unisiegen.tpml.core.typechecker.DefaultTypeCheckerProofNode
All Implemented Interfaces:
ProofNode, TypeCheckerProofNode, TreeNode
final class DefaultTypeCheckerProofNode
extends AbstractProofNode
implements TypeCheckerProofNode

Default implementation of the TypeCheckerProofNode interface. The class for nodes in a TypeCheckerProofModel.

Version:
$Rev: 307 $
Author:
Benedikt Meurer

getChildAfter

public DefaultTypeCheckerProofNode getChildAfter(TreeNode aChild)
Returns the child in this node's child array that immediately follows aChild, which must be a child of this node. If aChild is the last child, returns null. This method performs a linear search of this node's children for aChild and is O(n) where n is the number of children; to traverse the entire array of children, use an enumeration instead.
